                <note rend="inline" type="source">813.00/1170: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Curtis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-01-12T21:00:00-07:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 12, 1922—9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 13—12:13 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7. The Assembly this afternoon gave first of three daily readings to a resolution
                    reported by special committee declaring the Union non-existent and Guatemala
                    again an independent republic.</p>
                <p>General Orellana today issued a decree calling the elections for February 15th to
                    22nd. The Liberal Party will choose candidate January 22.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Curtis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
